{
  "texts": [
    "Relative advantage refers to the level to which an innovation is regarded as better than the idea it surpasses; stakeholders consider the benefits they will derive from it.",
    "Economic and social factors are measured including convenience and satisfaction.",
    "Compatibility refers to the level to which an innovation is believed to be consistent with the existing values, past experiences, and needs of prospective adopters (Rogers, 2003).",
    "If the innovation is not compatible with the norms and values of a social system, its adoption is inevitably slow.",
    "Complexity refers to the level to which an innovation is viewed to be difficult to understand and use."
  ]
}